[3] Saudi Arabia, 1 new case - MOH 20 Jun 2015, RFI
Date: 20 Jun 2015
Source: Saudi Arabia MOH [edited]
http://www.moh.gov.sa/en/CCC/PressReleases/Pages/Statistics-2015-06-20-001.aspx


As of 12:00 noon today, 20 Jun 2015, there have been a total of:
1038 laboratory-confirmed cases of MERS-CoV infection, including
459 deaths,
572 recoveries, and
7 currently active cases

In the past 24 hours there has been
1 newly confirmed case
0 new fatalities, and
1 new recovery

[Reported case fatality rate 44.2 percent]

Information on newly confirmed case:
A 60-year-old expat female healthcare worker from Hufoof noted to be in stable condition. At time of initial report, gave a history of contact with other case(s) in either the healthcare environment or the community.

Information on newly reported recovery:
A 60-year-old Saudi female, non-healthcare worker from Hufoof with a history of pre-existing co-morbidities. [Initially reported as a laboratory-confirmed case on 10 Jun 2015, at which time was noted to be in stable condition, and a possible history of contact with other case(s) was under review. - Mod.MPP]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The outbreak on Hufoof continues with 1 newly confirmed case in a healthcare worker and 1 fatality in a previously confirmed case. Using 20 Apr 2015 as the start date of this major outbreak in Hufoof, there have been 38 cases including 18 deaths (reported case fatality rate 47.4 percent).

Reviewing the information available on reported cases of MERS-CoV infection in Hufoof since 2014, it appears as though there were 2 presumably sporadic cases reported in 2014 -- one in July and one in October. Since the beginning of January there have been 45 cases including 20 deaths (reported case fatality rate 44.4 percent) reported from Hufoof. On 20 Jan 2015 there was a case reported that gave a history of exposure to camels during the 14 days preceding onset of illness. There were then cases reported on 2, 3, 24 Feb 2015, and 8, 14, 29 Mar 2015 with only the case reported on 24 Feb 2015 giving a history of contact with another MERS-CoV positive case in the healthcare environment. The next reported case was on 20 Apr 2015 -- 22 days after the last reported case. This case did not have a history of known high-risk exposures during the 14 days preceding onset of illness. Beginning 5 May 2015 through the present were reports of cases with either definite histories of contact with other cases -- initially "in the community" (having been identified as household contacts) and then in the healthcare environment. So the question that comes to mind is whether genetic profiles of the viruses involved in January, February and March 2015 have been done and likewise if studies on the viruses involved in April 2015 through the present have been done to see if the same lineages of virus were involved since January 2015 vs. multiple different viral introductions until April/May when the hospital associated outbreak has been defined as having begun. If any of our readers have information on this, ProMED would greatly appreciate receiving it.

A map showing the location of Hufoof in Saudi Arabia can be found at the source URL. - Mod.MPP]

